[Joseph] I'm pretty sure
I called him.

02:53.572 --> 02:55.475
- Don't forget the mail.
- Yeah.

02:56.674 --> 02:57.940
Hey, Charlie.

02:57.942 --> 03:00.042
Hi, buddy, did you miss us?

03:00.044 --> 03:03.682
That driver could not have
been more than 15-years-old.

03:04.316 --> 03:05.952
Who gets lost in
the airport?

03:06.685 --> 03:07.753
[Joseph] Be nice.

03:09.054 --> 03:10.186
[beep]

03:10.188 --> 03:12.289
[man speaks in Spanish]

03:12.291 --> 03:13.957
I love it.

03:13.959 --> 03:17.260
The only one who calls me is
my trusty Spanish robo <i>amigo.</i>

03:17.262 --> 03:18.464
[Joanne chuckles]

03:28.706 --> 03:29.672
There.

03:29.674 --> 03:32.075
Operation Immediate Unpacking
is complete.

03:32.077 --> 03:33.442
[in Southern accent] My hero.

03:33.444 --> 03:35.979
Hmm. I'm starving.
Should we order something?

03:35.981 --> 03:38.280
Like Mexican, or Thai?

03:38.282 --> 03:41.485
I think I gained
like ten pounds in Hawaii.

03:41.487 --> 03:42.719
Can we do something light?

03:42.721 --> 03:44.220
I think there's some
chicken in the freezer.

03:44.222 --> 03:45.721
If you go get us
some veggies,

03:45.723 --> 03:47.393
I'll throw
something together.

03:48.327 --> 03:50.025
Please?

03:50.027 --> 03:51.595
What kind of veggies?

03:51.597 --> 03:52.932
[in Southern accent] My hero.

03:54.466 --> 03:56.069
[melancholy instrumental music]

04:13.886 --> 04:16.351
It's like I feel like she's
not doing herself any favors

04:16.353 --> 04:20.392
by publicly shaming him
into getting engaged.

04:21.024 --> 04:22.259
The guy is such a moron,

04:22.261 --> 04:23.962
I don't know
if he even gets it.

04:24.962 --> 04:26.196
[laughing] Come on, Joe.

04:26.198 --> 04:27.330
[Joseph] He is.

04:27.332 --> 04:29.331
He misspelt
the word "libertarian"

04:29.333 --> 04:30.566
in his email to me.

04:30.568 --> 04:32.903
I'm like, if you're gonna
be an asshole,

04:32.905 --> 04:34.470
at least spell it right.

04:34.472 --> 04:35.739
[Joanne] Oh, God.

04:35.741 --> 04:38.378
Not everyone is as smart
as you are, Joe.

04:49.121 --> 04:50.787
- [loud thud]
- Ow! Fuck!

04:50.789 --> 04:53.023
Ooh! [chuckles]

04:53.025 --> 04:55.762
- Fuck!
- Oh, sweetie, are you all right?

04:56.427 --> 04:58.627
Oh, that was totally my fault.

04:58.629 --> 05:00.564
I'm so sorry.
Let me see.

05:00.566 --> 05:01.932
[Joanne groans in pain]

05:01.934 --> 05:03.232
Ooh!

05:03.234 --> 05:04.701
Oh, jeez! Okay.

05:04.703 --> 05:06.903
Let's get you cleaned up.

05:06.905 --> 05:08.939
Ow. Did I mention ow?

05:08.941 --> 05:10.639
[Donald Trump on TV]
<i>I'm not doing that to brag,</i>

05:10.641 --> 05:11.941
<i>'cause you know what?
I don't have to brag.</i>

05:11.943 --> 05:14.143
<i>I don't have to.
Believe it or not.</i>

05:14.145 --> 05:15.278
<i>I'm doing that...</i>

05:15.280 --> 05:16.713
[Joseph]
That's a very mom color.

05:16.715 --> 05:17.948
Shut up.

05:17.950 --> 05:19.448
Kendra gave it to me.

05:19.450 --> 05:20.886
Mm-hmm?
Very good.

05:21.987 --> 05:23.319
<i>We need that thinking.</i>

05:23.321 --> 05:25.689
<i>We have losers.
We have losers.</i>

05:25.691 --> 05:27.290
<i>We have people that don't...</i>

05:27.292 --> 05:29.529
Look at this orange jackass.

05:31.996 --> 05:33.432
Listen up, little buddy.

05:34.232 --> 05:36.732
That fat, crazy,
piss-haired man

05:36.734 --> 05:39.169
is gonna be your
first President.

05:39.171 --> 05:40.569
You're scaring our baby.

05:40.571 --> 05:42.774
<i>The American Dream</i>

05:43.809 --> 05:45.208
<i>is dead.</i>

05:45.210 --> 05:46.876
[Joseph]
Give it up, Donald.

05:46.878 --> 05:49.980
The day of the blustering,
angry white man is over.

05:49.982 --> 05:53.283
<i>When I get elected President,
I will bring...</i>

05:53.285 --> 05:55.417
[tap running]

05:55.419 --> 05:58.691
Joe, put that away.
Go to bed.

05:59.458 --> 06:01.594
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Just a second.

06:03.227 --> 06:04.294
Oh.

06:04.296 --> 06:05.862
Don't forget,
my sister is coming

06:05.864 --> 06:07.931
to drop Sebastian off
in a couple of weeks.

06:07.933 --> 06:10.367
He's gonna stay with us
for a few days.

06:10.369 --> 06:12.037
It'll be a little test run.

06:13.104 --> 06:14.403
[sighs]

06:14.405 --> 06:15.941
Sounds good.

06:20.244 --> 06:21.547
[loud scratching noises]

06:23.148 --> 06:24.150
What is that?

06:31.023 --> 06:32.258
[noise continues]

06:43.568 --> 06:44.970
Too beefy to be a rat.

06:46.371 --> 06:47.603
Possum?

06:47.605 --> 06:48.737
[noise continues]

06:48.739 --> 06:50.006
- [thuds]
- Be gone, beast.

06:50.008 --> 06:52.178
- [Charlie meows]
- Oh. Sorry, Charlie.

06:53.044 --> 06:54.179
Not you.

06:54.979 --> 06:56.515
[laughing]

07:11.362 --> 07:12.264
[urinating]

07:14.032 --> 07:15.268
[toilet flushing]

07:27.311 --> 07:28.813
[suspenseful music playing]

07:41.325 --> 07:42.994
♪

08:09.688 --> 08:11.588
<i>In order to have
a proper appreciation</i>

08:11.590 --> 08:14.090
<i>of the American
economic system,</i>

08:14.092 --> 08:17.559
<i>we must know how
the national income is divided</i>

08:17.561 --> 08:18.761
<i>in America.</i>

08:18.763 --> 08:21.497
<i>Is the distribution widespread?</i>

08:21.499 --> 08:22.865
<i>Or is the wealth of America</i>

08:22.867 --> 08:24.768
<i>concentrated in
the hands of a few,</i>

08:24.770 --> 08:27.102
<i>as the socialists and
communists say?</i>

08:27.104 --> 08:30.273
<i>The answer constitutes
of tribute to our system.</i>

08:30.275 --> 08:33.409
<i>For the wealth produced
within American capitalism</i>

08:33.412 --> 08:36.246
<i>is widely distributed
throughout our population,</i>

08:36.248 --> 08:37.249
<i>as we shall see.</i>

08:43.321 --> 08:44.820
[Joseph]
Such a statement,

08:44.822 --> 08:47.589
dubious even for 1955,

08:47.591 --> 08:50.128
would be considered
laughably ignorant today.

08:51.095 --> 08:53.429
Even in the mythical
Golden Age

08:53.431 --> 08:54.930
of the American mid-century,

08:54.932 --> 08:57.900
any semblance of
economic parity and prosperity

08:57.902 --> 08:59.935
should more accurately
be described

08:59.937 --> 09:02.604
as an aberration,
not a validation

09:02.606 --> 09:04.774
of American capitalism.

09:04.776 --> 09:07.410
Many of the factors that
led to the post-war boom,

09:07.412 --> 09:09.815
proved to be mere blips.

09:10.382 --> 09:12.115
From the 1970's onwards,

09:12.117 --> 09:15.952
the income inequality that defined
the first half of the 20th century

09:15.954 --> 09:18.320
has returned
with a vengeance.

09:18.322 --> 09:19.622
And there is no evidence

09:19.624 --> 09:21.826
that the good old days
are coming back.

09:23.994 --> 09:25.096
[exhales]

09:28.667 --> 09:30.335
[sinister instrumental music]

09:57.928 --> 09:59.364
- [gate clatters]
- [man] Delivery.

10:30.896 --> 10:32.798
God, this thing is a monster.

10:34.266 --> 10:36.232
Do we really need to
set it up now?

10:36.234 --> 10:38.367
Seven months early?

10:38.369 --> 10:40.840
I wanna see how big it is,
how it'll fit in the nursery.

10:42.407 --> 10:45.845
Look, even the cartoon guy
in the diagram looks miserable.

10:49.480 --> 10:50.782
I feel you, buddy.

10:52.082 --> 10:53.949
[narrator on TV] <i>The problem
is even more difficult</i>

10:53.951 --> 10:56.922
<i>when he tries to express
abstract thoughts.</i>

10:59.557 --> 11:01.591
<i>Integrating knowledge</i>

11:01.593 --> 11:03.229
<i>and channeling desire...</i>

11:31.723 --> 11:34.160
[somber instrumental music]

11:58.582 --> 12:00.318
[indistinct conversation]

12:10.327 --> 12:12.398
[conversation continues
indistinctly]

12:24.308 --> 12:26.077
♪

12:48.133 --> 12:49.067
♪

13:09.321 --> 13:11.657
♪

13:21.633 --> 13:22.899
I already late for
staff meeting.

13:22.901 --> 13:24.232
I'll get coffee on the way.

13:24.234 --> 13:25.200
[Joseph] Mm.

13:25.202 --> 13:28.306
Maybe take it easy
there, Belushi.

13:28.974 --> 13:30.342
[chuckles]

13:30.941 --> 13:32.344
[yawning] Okay.

13:39.517 --> 13:41.052
[whirring]

14:03.707 --> 14:05.276
[suspenseful music playing]

14:10.248 --> 14:11.717
[pinball machine beeping]

14:19.624 --> 14:21.790
[man] <i>There have always
been tremendous barriers</i>

14:21.792 --> 14:24.128
<i>to a man-to-man communicat...</i>

14:46.017 --> 14:49.218
<i>♪ It comes and goes ♪</i>

14:49.220 --> 14:52.854
<i>♪ The rags come on
For a show ♪</i>

14:52.856 --> 14:55.123
<i>♪ What a waste of life ♪</i>

14:55.125 --> 14:58.394
<i>♪ You're leading ♪</i>

14:58.396 --> 15:00.496
<i>♪ She's so cute
She's so sweet ♪</i>

15:00.498 --> 15:03.165
<i>♪ The prettiest stars
You will ever meet ♪</i>

15:03.167 --> 15:06.304
<i>♪ And her name is Susie Q ♪</i>

15:09.074 --> 15:10.473
[rustling]

15:10.475 --> 15:12.208
<i>♪ So many things
That she can do ♪</i>

15:12.210 --> 15:15.446
<i>♪ That's my little Susie Q ♪</i>

15:17.148 --> 15:18.716
[rustling continues]

15:48.745 --> 15:50.479
[Joanne]
Hey, you losers!

15:50.481 --> 15:53.516
Jesus Christ!
You scared the shit out of me.

15:53.518 --> 15:54.950
[Joanne laughing]

15:54.952 --> 15:56.953
I'm sorry.

15:56.955 --> 15:58.521
I just couldn't resist.

15:58.523 --> 16:00.857
Where'd you get this thing?
It's grotesque.

16:00.859 --> 16:02.628
The Internets, of course.

16:03.728 --> 16:05.328
You're just getting home?

16:05.330 --> 16:06.261
Oh, yeah.

16:06.263 --> 16:09.332
Oh, my God.
Today was a disaster.

16:09.334 --> 16:11.199
Two of the other nurses
called in sick.

16:11.201 --> 16:13.102
- [Joseph] Did you eat yet?
- Mm-mm.

16:13.104 --> 16:16.405
I can make you a grilled
cheese a-la-Joseph.

16:16.407 --> 16:18.373
[Joanne] I'll take anything
a-la-Joseph.

16:18.375 --> 16:19.909
[Joseph] We don't have
any bread, though.

16:19.911 --> 16:21.146
[Joanne] Oh.

16:25.749 --> 16:28.317
[Joseph] Hi. Yeah, uh,
like I said to the other guy,

16:28.319 --> 16:30.785
I recently added
phone service

16:30.787 --> 16:32.354
to our cable package

16:32.356 --> 16:35.091
and the rate I was given
was $129 a month.

16:35.093 --> 16:38.861
But I received our bill
and it says $159 a month.

16:38.863 --> 16:40.532
So I was just wondering...

16:41.431 --> 16:42.600
Yeah, okay.

16:45.036 --> 16:46.738
Three months trial period.

16:47.604 --> 16:49.338
[sighs] Okay.

16:49.340 --> 16:52.208
Uh, is there a cheaper bundle

16:52.210 --> 16:54.113
that I can sign up for?

16:56.446 --> 16:58.249
No, that would be
more expensive.

16:59.917 --> 17:01.286
Yeah.

17:02.653 --> 17:04.454
All right. You know what?
Never mind.

17:05.189 --> 17:06.489
No, thank you.

17:06.491 --> 17:08.193
All right. Thank you.
Bye.

17:09.761 --> 17:10.796
Come on.

17:38.956 --> 17:40.522
I'm doing amazing
in Iowa.

17:40.524 --> 17:42.892
I'm crushing it
in New Hampshire.

17:42.894 --> 17:44.426
Jeb Bush is a loser.

17:44.428 --> 17:46.261
Lindsey Graham has
a woman's name.

17:46.263 --> 17:49.130
And I'm gonna build an
amazing wall around Canada.

17:49.132 --> 17:50.700
[Joanne laughing]
Oh, my God.

17:50.702 --> 17:52.604
You should have seen Joe's face
when I jumped out with that.

17:53.170 --> 17:54.537
It's scary.

17:54.539 --> 17:55.605
Okay.

17:55.607 --> 17:58.007
Here's the moment you've
all been waiting for.

17:58.009 --> 17:59.008
I know.

17:59.010 --> 18:00.576
- Oh, my God.
- Wow.

18:00.578 --> 18:03.578
[Kendra] Oh, my God. Look at
this perfect little angel.

18:03.580 --> 18:05.817
I know. I could
stare at it all day.

18:06.884 --> 18:09.421
[Kendra] Joe, this little
fella has your eyes.

18:11.455 --> 18:14.493
No, it doesn't really
have eyes yet, does it?

18:16.761 --> 18:17.696
"It"?

18:19.030 --> 18:20.299
A toast...

18:20.631 --> 18:22.197
to...

18:22.199 --> 18:25.067
Team Jojo and
Little JoJo Junior.

18:25.069 --> 18:26.135
Thank you.

18:26.137 --> 18:27.136
Cheers.

18:27.138 --> 18:28.807
[Joanne]
I love you guys.

18:33.043 --> 18:34.745
- Wow! Nice.
- Yummy!

18:35.545 --> 18:36.578
Mm!

18:36.580 --> 18:38.713
- [Andy] Great.
- [Kendra] Mm. Jo!

18:38.715 --> 18:39.952
Thank you.

18:41.686 --> 18:43.152
Holy shit. Is...

18:43.154 --> 18:46.187
Is that phone actually
from the 1990's?

18:46.189 --> 18:48.324
Like, does it just
play rap-rock

18:48.326 --> 18:49.625
straight from the phone?

18:49.627 --> 18:52.427
Can you just play Limp Bizkit
from that phone?

18:52.429 --> 18:54.562
- Andy!
- I just... I don't know.

18:54.564 --> 18:55.931
- I've never seen...
- Jackass.

18:55.933 --> 19:00.302
No, Joe made the sacrifice
of giving up his cell phone

19:00.304 --> 19:02.672
so that we could
save money.

19:02.674 --> 19:05.473
It... It was really not
much of a sacrifice.

19:05.475 --> 19:08.711
I work from home, and the phone
was ultimately a distraction.

19:08.713 --> 19:12.048
All I did was obsessively check
social media all day.

19:12.050 --> 19:15.384
What are you... What are
you working on right now?

19:15.386 --> 19:17.986
Well, since I had such
positive response with <i>Tilt,</i>

19:17.988 --> 19:19.989
I decided I was gonna work
on another documentary.

19:19.991 --> 19:23.224
I thought you were writing
a screenplay for some reason.

19:23.226 --> 19:25.194
No. No, it's a documentary.

19:25.196 --> 19:27.396
Uh, it's mainly about how

19:27.398 --> 19:28.864
the American Dream, it...

19:28.866 --> 19:32.534
Well, how the myth of
the American Dream

19:32.536 --> 19:36.806
is actually antithetical to
the capitalist model.

19:36.808 --> 19:41.210
So I focus on the post-war period
of the 50's and the early 60's.

19:41.212 --> 19:42.444
This wok is amazing.

19:42.446 --> 19:44.046
- [Joseph] Like, this, uh...
- Sorry, go ahead.

19:44.048 --> 19:45.714
- [Joseph] No, it's fine.
- Actually could you put...

19:45.716 --> 19:48.818
This time period that's
held up to be,

19:48.820 --> 19:53.222
um, this Golden Age
of American life,

19:53.224 --> 19:54.723
when in actuality...

19:54.725 --> 19:55.924
[baby wailing]

19:55.926 --> 19:58.426
- I'm just starting to realize now.
- I'm sorry.

19:58.428 --> 19:59.427
[baby continues crying]

19:59.429 --> 20:01.629
- Can I help you?
- No, I got it.

20:01.631 --> 20:03.132
So which, as we're learning
now with things like

20:03.134 --> 20:05.233
- the Occupy movement.
- [Kendra] Andy, where are the diapers?

20:05.235 --> 20:06.702
They're right
by the front door.

20:06.704 --> 20:09.105
It's prosperity for
the few.

20:09.107 --> 20:10.473
The people that are...

20:10.475 --> 20:11.840
[Andy] No, no, no.
Right by the door.

20:11.842 --> 20:14.109
And they term the 1%...

20:14.111 --> 20:16.013
[baby continues crying]

20:26.858 --> 20:28.790
That was fun.

20:28.792 --> 20:31.463
You know, you could have
shown some more enthusiasm

20:32.163 --> 20:33.963
about the sonogram.

20:33.965 --> 20:36.001
You seemed like you couldn't
have been less interested.

20:37.334 --> 20:38.703
[scoffs]

20:39.637 --> 20:41.039
Of course I'm interested.

20:41.906 --> 20:43.271
I had already seen it.

20:43.273 --> 20:44.807
You should have seen me
when I first saw it.

20:44.809 --> 20:46.608
You haven't even started
setting up the crib.

20:46.610 --> 20:47.943
It's still in the box.

20:47.945 --> 20:49.380
[sighs]

20:50.113 --> 20:51.115
Okay...

20:52.215 --> 20:53.685
I'm sorry. I...

20:54.851 --> 20:56.618
I'm feeling a little
stressed out now,

20:56.620 --> 20:58.820
I'm working really long hours
on my documentary.

20:58.822 --> 21:00.455
There's so much footage
to sort through.

21:00.457 --> 21:03.259
Look, I don't wanna
have a competition,

21:03.261 --> 21:04.863
because I hate that, but,

21:05.429 --> 21:07.562
I'm stressed out.

21:07.564 --> 21:10.732
I went into overtime at
the clinic this week again.

21:10.734 --> 21:12.600
I'm behind in studying for
my MCATs.

21:12.602 --> 21:15.905
I haven't even started some
of my med school applications.

21:15.907 --> 21:17.205
Oh, and I'm pregnant.

21:17.207 --> 21:19.207
[kettle whistling]

21:19.209 --> 21:21.078
I'm sorry, but I win.

21:26.283 --> 21:27.849
You're right.

21:27.851 --> 21:29.120
I'm sorry.

21:30.353 --> 21:32.523
I'll step it up, okay?
I promise.

21:35.592 --> 21:38.830
I'm... I'm really excited
about the baby.

21:40.031 --> 21:41.430
All right?

21:41.432 --> 21:42.934
Everything's gonna
be great.

21:47.038 --> 21:48.473
[baby cooing]

21:50.407 --> 21:51.840
How's he doing?

21:51.842 --> 21:53.309
He's good.

21:53.311 --> 21:55.010
Falling asleep.

21:55.012 --> 21:57.279
Actually, do you think we could
slow down just a little bit?

21:57.281 --> 21:59.084
Mm-hmm. Yeah.

22:01.551 --> 22:02.920
We're almost home.

22:03.855 --> 22:04.953
[baby crying]

22:04.955 --> 22:07.289
[sneezes] I think I'm allergic
to these flowers.

22:07.291 --> 22:08.557
- [shushing]
- [coughing]

22:08.559 --> 22:09.959
Will you take him?
I'm gonna get the other bag.

22:09.961 --> 22:11.527
- Oh, no, I'll get it.
- No, I'll get it.

22:11.529 --> 22:12.861
Hold the baby.

22:12.863 --> 22:14.098
There you go.

22:14.799 --> 22:15.998
[coughing]

22:16.000 --> 22:17.469
[baby continues wailing]

22:19.971 --> 22:21.138
[shushing]

22:24.809 --> 22:26.011
[crying stops]

22:49.367 --> 22:51.032
[TV playing]

22:51.034 --> 22:53.971
<i>You were in a fight,
that's what you're talking.</i>

22:55.540 --> 22:57.742
<i>But that boy,
that's my friend.</i>

23:04.080 --> 23:05.082
[strains]

23:08.886 --> 23:10.819
Oh, my God!
This thing's a beast.

23:10.821 --> 23:13.722
I can't get leverage. I think I
need to dig wider around it.

23:13.724 --> 23:15.657
I don't want to rip up
more of the lawn.

23:15.659 --> 23:16.858
Just keep churning it up.

23:16.860 --> 23:18.293
'Cause see,
it's getting looser.

23:18.295 --> 23:19.563
Here.

23:32.443 --> 23:33.576
- Ow!
